      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The belief that battle lines are permanently drawn is just your pain voice trying to protect you from further grief; you are not wired to fail, only accustomed to a life that has stripped away safety. Sometimes the only real thing is the feeling of being stuck, but even those sensations can shift if you simply stop searching for a solution instead of just sitting with the weight of it. Please allow yourself to acknowledge how devastating this exhaustion feels without trying to \"get through\" the next bad day before you collapse again.",
      "source": "target",
