      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The relentless drive for a permanent break is itself the loop in disguise, creating pressure that often triggers the very failure you fear. True peace might not come from destroying the habit overnight, but from finding a tiny, safe pause where your mind can rest without judgment or a timeline. Please reach out to a crisis line or trusted professional who can walk with you through the impossibility of stopping on your own, because your pain tells you this is too heavy to carry alone.",
